commit 054878bc181e3ac88f1cf3e56a118ef11717d32a
Author: Richard Davison <richard.neil.davison@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 3 21:51:20 2026 -0500

    Revert next_action_time readback from Do_snipe_frame/Do_thief_frame effects (D2)

    C's do_snipe_frame/do_thief_frame read a stale next_action_time (OCaml
    decremented it but didn't write to C), causing wrong timer checks and
    corrupting OCaml's correct value on readback. OCaml already manages
    next_action_time directly (decrement + snipe_attack reset).

    This fixes the regression from 387589 to 387879 divergences.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

